          "username": "ml636r"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-30 11:27:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nthe log out put for sdc is already very large and i do not want to add more to it by changing the log level from debug to error.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "d8103d71c28a387475469e8299faa3103cefc89d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2737,
          "name": "Liang Ding",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liang.ding@intel.com",
          "username": "lding7"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-09 08:52:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHi, Michael\nIMHO, these logs are only output when some fatal errors happen. In normal case, these logs will not increase the log files. Moreover, if a developer find something wrong, it is hard for them to find root cause if they do not change these log level from debug to error manually, unfortunately, I did encounter this situation during my debugging, and I spent quite some time to change the log level and narrow down these issue gradually. If the log level were error instead of debug, I would fix my issue quickly. So I'd like to change the log level to save more time for developers.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "88d842c0f87a90a21d99c08f6d397ac018bf3577",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2737,
