        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-10 14:34:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\ni understand but i do not believe in over loading our log by default with all this info in case of an error by default.\nIn case of debugging a user can simply change the log level.\nThere were points where your change is welcomed and I marked them the other places please leave it as is.\nAs a general step for us in sdc if we want to debug we simply change the log level to debug.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "128a82fb6eb623559dfe8c6dee64f362409c0d85",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2737,
          "name": "Liang Ding",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liang.ding@intel.com",
          "username": "lding7"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-11 02:15:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nchanging the log level to debug would be the last thing I will do, it's definitely a nightmare especially for a new developer if you ever try it. That means developers have to search some logs they could be interested in in a huge number of log lines like finding a needle in a bundle of hay. For a sdc veteran like you, it may be easy as a pie, but for newcomers, it is not a friendly way to debug issues.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
